VALUES
(44, 14, 20, 44, 14, 6, 6, NULL, 'Journey to Lystra and Derbe', 'Both passages emphasize the cities of Lystra and Derbe, highlighting the geographical context of Paul''s missionary journey. The mention of Derbe in Acts 14:20 follows the reference to Lystra in Acts 14:6, illustrating the continuity of their travels.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 20, 44, 16, 40, 40, 'departed', 'Journey and Departure Motif', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of departure, highlighting the movement of Paul and his companions as they continue their mission. In Acts 14:20, Paul rises and departs with Barnabas, while in Acts 16:40, they comfort the brethren and then depart.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 20, 66, 11, 7, 12, 'rose up', 'Resurrection and Ascension Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection and ascension in both passages. In Acts, Paul rises after being stoned, while in Revelation, the two prophets are resurrected and ascend to heaven.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 44, 13, 51, 51, 'Iconium', 'Journey of Paul and Barnabas', 'Both passages emphasize the movement of Paul and Barnabas as they travel to different cities to preach the gospel. The mention of Iconium in both verses highlights their ongoing mission and the challenges they faced in spreading their message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 44, 14, 1, 1, 'preached the gospel to that city', 'Connection of Preaching in Iconium', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching the gospel in Iconium, leading to the belief of many. The return to Lystra and Iconium in Acts 14:21 suggests a continuation of their mission that began in Acts 14:1.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 40, 28, 19, 19, 'taught many', 'Commission to Preach and Teach', 'Both passages emphasize the act of teaching and spreading the gospel. Acts 14:21 describes the apostles preaching the gospel, while Matthew 28:19 commands to teach all nations, highlighting the continuity of the mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 44, 13, 14, 14, 'Antioch', 'Journey of Paul and Barnabas', 'Both passages emphasize the travels of Paul and Barnabas as they spread the gospel. Acts 14:21 mentions their return to cities where they had previously preached, including Antioch, which is introduced in Acts 13:14.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 44, 15, 36, 36, NULL, 'Connection of Missionary Visits', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of revisiting cities where the gospel was preached. This connection highlights Paul''s desire to check on the brethren in those areas.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 21, 55, 3, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Persecution Experiences', 'Both passages emphasize the locations of Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra, where Paul faced significant challenges. This connection highlights the continuity of Paul''s ministry and the adversities he endured in these cities.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 60, 5, 10, 10, 'through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God', 'Suffering and Strengthening in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering as a precursor to spiritual growth and stability. Acts 14:22 speaks of entering the kingdom of God through tribulation, while 1 Peter 5:10 highlights being perfected and strengthened after suffering.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 55, 3, 12, 12, 'through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God', 'Suffering for Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that believers will face tribulation and persecution as part of their faith journey. Acts 14:22 states that we must enter the kingdom through much tribulation, while 2 Timothy 3:12 asserts that all who live godly will suffer persecution.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'through much tribulation', 'Tribulation and Overcoming', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of tribulation in the believer''s life. Acts 14:22 states that we must enter the kingdom through much tribulation, while John 16:33 acknowledges tribulation in the world but encourages believers with the assurance of Christ''s victory.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 52, 3, 2, 4, 'through much tribulation', 'Afflictions and Tribulation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of tribulation faced by believers. Acts 14:22 states that ''through much tribulation'' believers enter the kingdom, while 1 Thessalonians 3:4 acknowledges that ''we should suffer tribulation.'' This connection highlights the shared theme of enduring hardships in faith.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 45, 8, 17, 17, 'through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God', 'Suffering and Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of suffering as part of the Christian experience. Acts 14:22 highlights that tribulation is essential for entering the kingdom, while Romans 8:17 connects suffering with future glorification.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 66, 2, 10, 10, 'through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God', 'Tribulation and Faithfulness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of enduring tribulation as part of the Christian faith. Acts 14:22 speaks of entering the kingdom through much tribulation, while Revelation 2:10 encourages faithfulness in the face of suffering.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 22, 55, 1, 8, 8, 'through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God', 'Afflictions and Tribulation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of enduring hardships in faith. Acts 14:22 speaks of entering the kingdom through tribulation, while 2 Timothy 1:8 encourages participation in afflictions for the gospel.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 56, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Ordination of Elders', 'Both passages emphasize the ordination of elders in churches. Acts 14:23 describes the process of appointing elders, while Titus 1:5 instructs Titus to ordain elders in every city.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 44, 11, 30, 30, 'elders', 'Connection of Elders in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the role of elders in the early church. Acts 14:23 mentions the ordination of elders, while Acts 11:30 refers to sending aid to the elders, highlighting their importance in church governance.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 59, 5, 14, 14, 'elders in every church', 'Role of Elders in Prayer', 'This connection highlights the role of elders in the church, as both passages emphasize their importance in prayer. Acts 14:23 mentions the ordination of elders, while James 5:14 calls for elders to pray over the sick.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 44, 20, 32, 32, 'commended them to the Lord', 'Commending to God', 'This connection highlights the act of commending believers to God in both passages. In Acts 14:23, the elders are commended to the Lord, while in Acts 20:32, Paul commends the brethren to God and His word.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 55, 2, 2, 2, 'ordained them elders in every church', 'Leadership and Teaching in the Church', 'This connection highlights the importance of establishing leaders in the church and the responsibility of those leaders to teach others. Both passages emphasize the commitment to faithful individuals who can continue the work of ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 54, 5, 22, 22, 'ordained them elders in every church', 'Connection of Ordination and Purity', 'This connection highlights the importance of careful selection in church leadership. Both passages emphasize the need for purity and discernment when appointing elders or laying hands on individuals.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 23, 54, 5, 1, 1, 'elders in every church', 'Elders and Their Treatment', 'This connection highlights the role of elders in the church. Both passages emphasize the importance of treating elders with respect and care, reflecting their ordained position.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 24, 44, 13, 13, 14, 'Pamphylia', 'Journey Through Pamphylia and Pisidia', 'Both passages emphasize the geographical journey of Paul and his companions through Pamphylia and Pisidia. The movement from Perga to Antioch in Pisidia in Acts 13:13-14 is directly followed by their passage through Pisidia in Acts 14:24.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 24, 44, 15, 38, 38, 'Pamphylia', 'Connection of Pamphylia in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize Pamphylia as a significant location in Paul''s journey. The mention of Pamphylia in Acts 14:24 sets the stage for the later reference in Acts 15:38 regarding John Mark''s departure from that area.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 44, 15, 40, 40, 'recommended to the grace of God', 'Connection of Grace Recommendations', 'Both passages emphasize being ''recommended to the grace of God,'' highlighting the communal support for the missions of Paul and his companions. This connection illustrates the importance of divine grace in their ministry efforts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 44, 11, 19, 19, 'the grace of God for the work', 'Connection of Mission and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the spread of the Gospel. Acts 11:19 describes the initial preaching efforts in Antioch, while Acts 14:26 highlights the fulfillment of the work that began there, underscoring the continuity of mission and divine grace.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 45, 15, 19, 19, 'recommended to the grace of God', 'Connection of Mission and Grace', 'This connection highlights the theme of being recommended to the grace of God for the work of preaching the gospel. Both passages emphasize the fulfillment of this mission through the power of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 47, 1, 12, 12, 'grace of God', 'Connection of Grace in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in the work of ministry. Acts highlights being recommended to the grace of God, while 2 Corinthians speaks of conducting oneself by the grace of God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 14, 26, 51, 1, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Ministry and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fulfilling a divinely appointed task. Acts 14:26 speaks of the work fulfilled by Paul and his companions, while Colossians 1:25 refers to fulfilling the word of God as part of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
